ZCZC GE12
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
MONDAY TO THURSDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND COASTGUARD AGENCY
AT 212300 UTC
THERE IS AN ANTICYCLONE CENTRED OVER THE BALTIC SEA WHICH EXTENDS A RIDGE
SW ACROSS THE BRITISH ISLES. THIS RIDGE REMAINS SLOW MOV ON MONDAY THROUGH
TO TUESDAY AND THEN SLWY MOVS E BY OVERNIGHT INTO WEDNESDAY. A WEAK TROUGH
MOVS IN FM THE W ON TUESDAY EVENING AND INTO WEDNESDAY MORNING. THE TROUGH
SLWY MOVS SE AND MOVS AWAY TO THE E ON THURSDAY. STRG TO NEAR GALES ACROSS
NERN AREAS FOR MONDAY EVENING WITH GALES EXP IN THE FAR NE ALONG THE COAST
OF NORWAY. GALES WILL EASE TUESDAY MORNING BUT WINDS WILL REMAIN STRG BY
TUESDAY MIDDAY. GALES REDEVELOP IN THE FAR NE TUESDAY EVENING AND THROUGH
TO WEDNESDAY MORNING. WINDS WILL REMAIN BELOW FCST CRITERIA THROUGH TO THURSDAY
MORNING AND AFTERNOON. STRG TO NEAR GALE WINDS WILL DEVELOP AGAIN IN THE
FAR NE BY THURSDAY EVENING
